				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">You need a 4th wire for ground too, is that connected?<br /><br />The latch signal is sent before reading the controllers.  Look up the CD4021 to see how the protocol works (latch is connected to parallel load).  The NES doesn't need to read the data immediately after latching, the same latch signal is used for both controllers, also other things are possible like having latch remain active so the NES would only be reading the A button repeatedly.  Games that use DPCM will also read the controllers repeatedly, discarding reads that don't match.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

